 "Just... imagine the chances. When our world exploded into being, it 
could have blown us apart to the furthest corners of the universe... the pieces
that make us now would never have come together. But that didn't happen. 
Fate drove us here. And here we are, together." 
 He took her hands in his, the candle in the room flickering to some unfelt 
gust of air.
 "I was with you in the beginning, Leiana, just like I'll be with you in the
end. When the world stops." He drew up closer to her.
 "But I'm here now too, I'm here for these moments inbetween. And that means 
something."
